the 2010 aegon championships (also known traditionally as the queen's club championships) was a tennis tournament played on outdoor grass courts. it was the 39th edition of the aegon championships and was part of the atp world tour 250 series of the 2010 atp world tour. it took place at the queen's club in london, united kingdom, from june 7 through june 13, 2010. the field was headlined by the 2008 champion and current world number one rafael nadal, novak djokovic, andy roddick and defending champion andy murray.